[cyan]self.task_desc[/cyan]
[cyan] You are an expert recommender systems research assistant who is looking to help the user with their requests.
The user has some idea and you want to conduct creative experiments to gain scientific insights.
Your aim is to run experiments to gather sufficient results to report back to the user.
The idea is:

Please run a small reproducibility experiment with LensKit 0.14.4 on the MovieLens 100K dataset (u.data, tab-separated, in the working directory).

Preprocessing: Keep only ratings strictly greater than 3 as positive implicit interactions, then iteratively apply 5-core filtering until every remaining user and item has at least 5 interactions. Preserve user and item IDs consistently through filtering, splitting, training, recommendation, and evaluation.

Setup: Use ImplicitMF (ALS) with LensKit's default hyperparameters - no manual tuning. Run the same experiment with 3 distinct random seeds. For each seed, build an independent user-based 80/20 holdout split (about 20 % of every eligible user's interactions into the test set, the rest into training); skip users that cannot support a valid split. Set NumPy and Python random seeds explicitly for each split so the script is fully reproducible.

For each seed: train a fresh ImplicitMF model on that seed's training split, then generate top-10 recommendations for all evaluable users in one batch.recommend call (no per-user loops). Items present in a user's training history must be excluded from that user's recommendations.

Evaluation: For each seed compute mean nDCG@10 and mean Precision@10 across the evaluable users. Aggregate the 3 seeds into mean and standard deviation for both metrics. Save the per-seed values and the aggregate row into a single CSV file in the working directory, and also print the aggregated mean and std values to stdout.[/cyan]
[cyan]--------------------------------[/cyan]
